bio.experienceSummary:
I'm a childcare provider with a deep-rooted passion for nurturing children's growth and development. With over three years of experience, I'm skilled at creating a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment for children.

Patient, calm, and creative, I'm adept at engaging children with various activities that foster their learning and social skills. I believe in open and consistent communication with parents and prioritize following their preferred communication method.

I'm well-versed in enforcing household rules and ensuring children's safety. From outdoor sports to educational games, I enjoy a wide range of activities and adapt them to children's interests and abilities.

I'm comfortable caring for one child at a time and am happy to assist with cooking, meal preparation, and light housekeeping. I'd love the opportunity to create a wonderful bond with your children and cultivate a fun, educational, and safe space for them when I'm around.

I've always been passionate about nurturing the growth and development of children, which led me to pursue a career as a childcare provider. With my calm and patient demeanor, I strive to create a safe and nurturing environment for children to thrive.

I believe in open and honest communication with parents, ensuring they are regularly updated about their child's day and any matters that arise. I am comfortable enforcing household rules while maintaining a positive and respectful atmosphere.

From outdoor sports to technology-based games, I enjoy engaging children in various activities that spark their curiosity and creativity.

As a reliable childcare provider, I am comfortable caring for up to five children of all ages. With some college education and various certifications, including CPR training and First Aid, I am well-equipped to handle any situation that may arise.

I have a car, am comfortable with pets, and have a flexible schedule that can accommodate your family's needs.

Hi, I'm an experienced babysitter who genuinely loves working with kids. I'm fun, patient, and responsible, always making sure your child feels safe and cared for. I'm fluent in both English and Spanish, which helps me connect with families from different backgrounds. I have great recommendations and am a reliable driver if transportation is needed. I'm dependable, respectful, and patient; qualities that help me create a calm, secure environment for your child.

I started working with kids at 19 and now have children of my own, ages 17 and 15. Since becoming a parent, I've been babysitting part-time, gaining hands-on experience with kids of all ages. In my spare time, I enjoy walking, crocheting, crafting, and finding new music for my piano students.

My top three child care skills are patience, adaptability, and being hands-on. I'm adaptable to unexpected situations, patient with kids' needs, and hands-on to keep them engaged and safe.

Hi there! I am an outgoing, empathetic public servant with 10+ years of experience caring for children ages 6 weeks to 14 years old. I have served in several positions pertaining to child and youth engagement, including as a nanny, camp counselor, mentor, and day camp director. I always ensure that the children I work with feel uplifted and supported, and am take care to cultivate creative, interactive activities and opportunities for engagement, whether through crafts, guitar, reading, games, and outdoor play. Most recently, I served as a longterm nanny (first full-time, then part-time) for three years for a private household on the Upper East Side with two children ages 2 and 4 at start. They found me through Care. com, actually! I also spent two years as a babysitter for two children, aged six weeks and four years to start, while studying at Bard College. I am open to evening, weekend, and when-needed opportunities in the New York City area.

Hi! My name is Brady. I have played soccer most of my life so I love to be active, do arts and crafts and play games. I am caring, responsible, and fun. I thoroughly enjoy my job and families have appreciated my flexibility, responsiveness to the child and parents, and the pleasure I took in being with their children.

Hello, my name is Sally. I was born in 1964 and am a married woman originally from the Philippines and now a legal United States citizen permanently living in New York City with my husband, a retired public school principal. I have many successful years being a nanny with from one to two children. I was nanny to one little girl whose family lives on the Upper West Side. I raised her from 2 months to six years of age until she started school. My services were no longer needed, however, I was considered part of the family and still keep in touch. I am reliable, loving, trustworthy and intelligent. I'm looking for a family that will treat me with kindness, respect and dignity. In return, I will take care of their child or children as though they were my own. Please contact me if interested. References available upon request. Thank you.

I have 8 years of various experience in childcare including part time nannying, full time nannying, and 3 years as a summer camp counselor and supervisor. I have worked with children of all ages from newborn to 15 years. 

My childcare philosophy is that a child learns best by experience. That is why I believe that it is crucial to expose children to the world around them through exploration activities. Any activity that takes a child out into the world can become a learning experience. For younger children, it could be socialization or learning to behave appropriately in public settings. For older children, it could be learning how to budget at the grocery store or how to determine the appropriate tip for a service employee. Every activity or errand can become a learning experience for children of any age whether that's a day trip to a museum or just a quick trip to the store. I strongly believe that the best time to teach a child is when the child doesn't realize they're learning.

Hi, I'm Shauna! I am an experienced and nurturing nanny with 15 years of hands-on experience caring for children of all ages, from newborns to teenagers.

Skilled in providing a safe, stimulating, and educational environment while fostering emotional and social development. Proficient in managing daily routines, including meal preparation, homework assistance, and organizing age-appropriate activities. Committed to creating a positive and supportive atmosphere for children and families. Reliable, patient, and passionate about child development. CPR and First Aid certified, valid drivers license and passport.

description.displayText: Shauna is an absolutely wonderful nanny, and we feel lucky to have her in our lives.  Shauna watched my daughter full time from ages 5 months to 18 months.  As first time parents, my husband and I were thankful every day to have Shauna's experience and sound judgment to complement our parenting.  She planned and prepared healthy and fun meals, starting from  introduction of purees to fully rounded meals as my daughter got older.  Shauna read her countless books, took her on adventures around the city, sparked her imagination, and was an overall best friend, mentor, and companion to my little gal.  We were all shocked when we realized that my 18 month old knew all of her letters!  It was all Shauna's daily engagement and teaching.  She kept the house neat and tidy, picked up groceries when we were too busy to make it out, reminded us to increase the flow on the bottle and size up in diapers... When we decided to move out of New York and relocate across the country, leaving Shauna was by far the hardest part of the decision.  It had been our every intention that she would watch all of our future children and be a part of our family well into the future.  She helped us with the move, even coming to Texas for a week to train our new nanny and help my daughter transition.  We are still in close touch with Shauna and my daughter adores the FaceTime sessions they have.  Any family is lucky to have Shauna as a nanny or babysitter!

bio.experienceSummary:
Experience nanny and childcare of two boy.
Occasionally babysit for 8 months old and 4 years old girls.
Occasionally helped with child care for family date night. 
Cook and feed the child and play with them.
Read them story!

Hi, my name is Shivanie! I am a registered nurse with two prior bachelor degrees. I am a passionate, empathetic & patient young woman who I hope you will trust with your childcare. I love to be actively involved in playtime activities, and safety is always the top priority! 

Babysitting experience includes providing childcare for various families in my neighborhood, both on a consistent basis & intermittently, with children as young as 2 months. Additional experience includes teaching dance classes for children ages ranging from 2-10. I have experience with infants, as well as with children with special needs & caring for twins. 

I am comfortable with some light meal prep/ cooking and cleaning, and open to school and/or extracurricular activity pickups, as well as homework help. I have my own car as well, so transportation will be no problem!

description.originalText: Shivanie has a warm, playful demeanor and our son took to her right away.  She jumped right in and we could tell that he was comfortable which put us at ease.  I would highly recommend her.
